[inference]
template_type: WordAct
lexicon_terms: [observe, assess, plan, act, monitor, recall, discover]
contract:
  input: {subjective: string, profile_block: string, severity_block: string, samples_table: string, freshness: string, events_table: string, reflex_section: string|null, actionable_skills: array|null, knowledge_skills: array|null, hkask_tools: array|null}
  output: {rendered_prompt: string}

---
{# hKask v0.28.0 — A Minimal Viable Container for Replicants #}
# SOAP — russell help

## Subjective

{{ subjective }}

## Objective

### Profile
{{ profile_block }}

### Severity counts — last 24h
{{ severity_block }}

### Host probe samples — last 24h
{{ samples_table }}

### Sentinel freshness
{{ freshness }}
{% if actionable_skills %}

### Available skills
| skill | type | id | risk |
|---|---|---|---|
{% for s in actionable_skills %}{% for p in s.probes %}| {{ s.id }} | probe | {{ p.id }} | none |
{% endfor %}{% for iv in s.interventions %}| {{ s.id }} | intervention | {{ iv.id }} | {{ iv.risk }} |
{% endfor %}{% endfor %}
When you identify a next step and a skill is loaded, propose it on the final line using ACTION syntax:

For probes (read-only, auto-execute): ACTION: <skill-id>/<probe-id>
(e.g. ACTION: inference-watcher/probe-health)

For interventions (mutations, require consent): ACTION: <skill-id>/<intervention-id>
(e.g. ACTION: inference-watcher/reset-backend)

Prefer probes first to gather evidence. Probes run immediately. Interventions wait for the operator to say 'ok'.
{% endif %}
{% if knowledge_skills %}

### Loaded knowledge
The following knowledge skills are active (their expertise is in your system prompt):
{% for k in knowledge_skills %}{% if k.symptoms %}- **{{ k.id }}** — symptoms: {{ k.symptoms }}
{% else %}- **{{ k.id }}**
{% endif %}{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% if hkask_tools %}

### HKask MCP tools
| tool | risk |
|---|---|
{% for t in hkask_tools %}| {{ t.name }} | {{ t.risk }} |
{% endfor %}
You can also call HKask tools via ACTION syntax:
ACTION: hkask/<tool-name>
(e.g. ACTION: hkask/paradigm_shift_query)

If the tool needs arguments, add an Arguments line:
Arguments: {"prompt": "...", "depth": "quick"}

Tools with risk 'none' auto-execute. Others require operator consent.
{% endif %}

### Most-recent events (up to 20)
{{ events_table }}
{% if reflex_section %}

{{ reflex_section }}
{% endif %}

